// Virtual main: exit code = ok arm (7) + err arm (99) == 106. Reaching it forces the inline
// `i64 | error` variant (typedef + wrap + match discrimination) through the checker, VM and
// codegen. A clean exit 106 on BOTH the VM (`teko run`) and the compiled binary proves the
// inline-union tagged-union lowering holds.
use m

(m::classify_ok() + m::classify_err()) to i32
